Flickr Module
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A plugin for Croogo CMS for displaying random flickr PUBLIC photos of a given user in a block.


REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    - Testing with CakePHP 2.2.3 & Croogo 1.4.2
    - A Flickr User ID. The flickr account that owns the photos.
    - IMPORTANT. A Flickr API Key. It defaults to a key for this Croogo plugin. If you are going
      to ship your app commercially, I ask you to change it. This default key is for non-commercial
      apps only.  You can get a flickr API key from http://www.flickr.com/services/api/

    Hint: If you don't know how to get the flickr user id, you can use the following
    service: http://idgettr.com/


HOW TO USE
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    1. Log in to admin panel
    2. Go to Extensions > Plugins page
    3. Upload the zip file (available here)
    4. Click on tick/cross icon of 'FlcikrModule' for activating or deactivating the plugin
    5. Go to menu Extensions > Flickr Module > Configure and put your settings.
    6. Enjoy!


Assumptions
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    - You are using jQuery.

